## Rust Edition vs Version (Important Distinction)

| Term | What it means | Current value |
|------|--------------|---------------|
| **Rust Version** (compiler) | The rustc version (1.83, 1.84, etc.) | Always use **latest stable** |
| **Rust Edition** | Language dialect set in Cargo.toml | **2021** (current mainstream) |

### Why Edition 2021 (not 2024)?

- **Existing project uses it** — All Cargo.toml files specify `edition = "2021"`
- **Ecosystem stability** — Edition 2024 (released Nov 2024) may have compatibility gaps
- **syn 2.x compatibility** — syn 2.x works perfectly with edition 2021
- **No 2024 features needed** — proc-macro development doesn't require 2024's new features

### Edition 2024 Changes (not needed here)

- `gen` keyword reservation
- RPIT lifetime capture changes
- `unsafe_op_in_unsafe_fn` becomes deny-by-default
- Prelude changes

**Note**: "Rust stable (edition 2021)" means latest stable compiler + edition 2021 language features.

